snippet.textDisplay: Actually, Marsh is one of my favorites, the chorus is super catchy and most of those "corny lines" you mentioned in Marsh and others don't really seem that corny at all, to me at least. Also, my favorite chorus are probably from I Will, Marsh and Unaccomodating just because I find them so catchy and can't get them out of my head, which is kinda funny because those are the one you stood out as bad. Well, I guess taste really is subjective! He's rarely direct in his verses so having more basic yet cool lines is typical of him and don't really think it instantly means they are "corny", he's also always had those "corny" lines throughout his career for humor or style purposes and I think that's what happens here too, hence me not thinking they're "corny". I think most of them at least are on purpose for stylistic reasons like we've always seen from him. But ya know, just wanted to leave that thought here and my personal experience with the album! Have a good day.

snippet.textDisplay:
To be fair, you have to have a very high IQ to understand Music to Be Murdered By. The album is extremely subtle, and without a solid grasp of theoretical musicology most of the songs will go over a typical listener’s head. There’s also Marshall’s nihilistic outlook, which is deftly woven into his characterisation- his personal philosophy draws heavily from Drug abuse, for instance. The fans understand this stuff; they have the intellectual capacity to truly appreciate the depths of these bars, to realise that they’re not just pleasing to the ear- they say something deep about LIFE. As a consequence people who dislike Eminem truly ARE idiots- of course they wouldn’t appreciate, for instance, the humour in Eminem's existential catchphrase “Mom's spaghetti,” which itself is a cryptic reference to Pasolini’s Itialan Epic Essentials of Classic Italian Cooking. I’m smirking right now just imagining one of those addlepated simpletons scratching their heads in confusion as Marshall Mathers genius wit unfolds itself in their ears. What fools.. how I pity them.

And yes, by the way, i DO have a tattoo of his name across my chest. And no, you cannot see it. It’s for the ladies’ eyes only- and even then they have to demonstrate that they’re within 5 IQ points of my own (preferably lower) beforehand. Nothin personnel kid.
